{
  "id": "L2",
  "title": "Ordering at a Café",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome! In this lesson, you'll learn how to order a drink and a snack at a Spanish café. Let's start by getting the waiter's attention."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Perdón",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L2_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Perdón",
        "phonetic": "[peɾˈðon]",
        "tip": "The 'r' in 'Perdón' is a soft tap of the tongue against the roof of your mouth, similar to the 'tt' in the English word 'butter'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Quisiera...",
        "meaning": "I would like..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V01",
      "data": {
        "Un café": "A coffee"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V02",
      "data": {
        "Un té": "A tea"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Tiene...?",
        "meaning": "Do you have...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V03",
      "data": {
        "Tarta de manzana": "Apple pie"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L2_S01",
      "title": "Getting the waiter's attention",
      "setting": "You're at a café. It's time to get the waiter's attention and place your first order.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Get the waiter's attention"
        },
        {
          "title": "Order a drink",
          "chatbot_message": "Hola. Dígame."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if they have apple pie",
          "chatbot_message": "Un café. Muy bien. ¿Algo más?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Acknowledge the waiter",
          "chatbot_message": "Sí, tenemos tarta de manzana."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! In Spanish, nouns have a gender. 'Un' is used for masculine words like 'café', and 'una' for feminine words like 'tarta'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V04",
      "data": {
        "Una tarta": "A pie / a cake"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Por favor",
        "meaning": "Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Eso es todo",
        "meaning": "That is all"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V05",
      "data": {
        "Gracias": "Thank you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Dónde está el baño?",
        "meaning": "Where is the bathroom?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L2_S02",
      "title": "Ordering a snack",
      "setting": "The waiter has confirmed they have the pie you want. Now, order it and ask for the bathroom.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Order the apple pie"
        },
        {
          "title": "Confirm that is all you want",
          "chatbot_message": "Perfecto. Un café y una tarta de manzana. Ahora mismo. ... Aquí tiene."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask for the location of the bathroom",
          "chatbot_message": "De acuerdo."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the waiter",
          "chatbot_message": "El baño está al fondo a la derecha."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "You're doing great! To get the bill in Spain, you usually have to ask for it. The waiter won't bring it automatically."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "La cuenta, por favor",
        "meaning": "The bill, please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Cuánto es?",
        "meaning": "How much is it?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L2_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta?",
        "meaning": "Can I pay with a card?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V06",
      "data": {
        "Sí": "Yes"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L2_V07",
      "data": {
        "Adiós": "Goodbye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L2_S03",
      "title": "Paying the bill",
      "setting": "You've finished your coffee and pie. Now it's time to pay and leave.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask for the bill"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask how much it is",
          "chatbot_message": "Sí, claro. Aquí tiene."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if you can pay by card",
          "chatbot_message": "Son cinco euros."
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "Sí, por supuesto."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}